    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m0oxrnwj/529b2490-4fec-42e5-9e0d-d59742d7eeba/45c22130-6b54-11ef-a274-1114b595fa40/file-jaoe38c1m0oxrnwk.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m0oxrnwj/529b2490-4fec-42e5-9e0d-d59742d7eeba/45c22130-6b54-11ef-a274-1114b595fa40/file-jaoe38c1m0oxrnwk.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE CE 2022 Set 2 Structural Analysis - Stability and Static Indeterminacy Question 2 English Explanation\"></p>\n<p>Equilibrium reaction $=3$</p>\n<p>Degree of static indeterminacy,</p>\n<p>$$ D S I=R-3 \\Rightarrow 2 $$</p>\n<p>Kinematic indeterminacy, $K I=$ ?</p>\n<p>$\\because$ At simply supported only one chances of rotation or of is free to rotate.</p>\n<p>So, $ K I=1$</p>\n<p>Hence, the correct option is (D).</p>",
